Governor of Imo State, Rochas Okorocha has fired 13 political appointees in the state, with his son-in-law, Uche Nwosu also affected. The state government revealed this in a statement signed by Samuel Onwuemeodo, chief press secretary to the governor. According to the statement the affected appointees are those seeking elective positions on the platforms of the All Progressives Congress (APC). He listed those affected by the sack as: 